Cyril Ramaphosa says government is strengthening good governance models in all State owned entities. CAPE TOWN - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says government is strengthening good governance models in all state-owned entities and government departments.In the National Council of Provinces this afternoon he emphasised that government business should not be influenced by negative dynamics within the business sector.Ramaphosa said that all state institutions should function optimally if they adhere to the practice of good governance. We are certain that as all state institutions adhere to these, they will have the good shock absorbers as it were not to be susceptible to undue influences from outside. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)